abstract: Google said it needed time to resolve legal issues concerning Internet data inadvertently collected from home wireless networks.
snippet: Google said it needed time to resolve legal issues concerning Internet data inadvertently collected from home wireless networks.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN  Google has balked at requests from regulators to surrender Internet data and fragments of e-mail messages that it collected from unsecured home wireless networks, saying it needed time to resolve legal issues.

headline.main: Google Balks at Turning Over Private Internet Data to Regulators
headline.print_headline: Google Balks at Turning Over Private Internet Data to Regulators
